@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "TurnAbout" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile; if that part of the tile is next to
the empty space, the other portion of that tile will 'pivot'
towards the empty space. The former position occupied by the tile
will then be marked by a coloured octagonal shape.

  A tile located on an edge of the gameboard can pivot to the
other side of the board, provided, of course, that the empty
space is located on the same row or column, at the gameboard's
other edge...

  The main goal is to move the empty space on all positions of
the board, and the game is completed when the empty space is
located on the lower right position of the game board.

  The game can be restarted anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or by
pressing on the 'Esc' key.
    
